at approaches sex as a social practice with political and economic effects, Koch compellingly illustrates the linkages between women's work, sex, and the gendered economy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aProstituteszJapanzTokyo. 0aProstitutionzJapanzTokyo. 0aSex workerszJapanzTokyo. 0aSex-oriented businesseszJapanzTokyo. 0aWomenxEmploymentzJapanzTokyo. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aJapan.  acare.  afemale labor market.  agendered economy.  ahealing.  ahuman rights.  alabor rights.  asex industry.  asex work.  asex.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069218140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361135140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503611351423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503611351.jpg  a978-3-11-069218-1  SUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-SEWb2020